2C%20nose%2C%20and%20throat%20irritation%2C%20headaches%20and%20dizziness%2C%20even%20liver%20damage%20and%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20ways%20to%20remove%20VOCs%20from%20your%20home%20are%20opening%20the%20windows%20and%20getting%20rid%20of%20their%20sources%2C%20Glenn%20Morrison%2C%20a%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20environmental%20science%20and%20engineering%20professor%20who%20studies%20indoor%20air%20pollution%2C%20told%20BI.%20Some%20types%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-air-purifier%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emechanical%20air%20purifiers%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20remove%20them%20too%2C%20but%20many%20of%20them%20can%20produce%20other%20harmful%20chemicals%20like%20carbon%20monoxide%2C%20ozone%2C%20and%20formaldehyde.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Neoplants%20co-founders%20Patrick%20Torbey%20and%20Lionel%20Mora%20weren't%20satisfied%20with%20these%20options.%20They%20argue%20that%20opening%20windows%20only%20temporarily%20reduces%20indoor%20pollution%20to%20outside%20levels%2C%20and%20not%20everyone%20can%20easily%20get%20rid%20of%20VOC%20sources%20in%20their%20homes.%20What's%20more%2C%20they%20believe%20existing%20VOC-removing%20technologies%20aren't%20worth%20their%20drawbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20they%20turned%20to%20biology%20to%20invent%20their%20own%20solution.%20The%20result%2C%20%3Cspan%3ENeoPx%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20is%2030%20times%20more%20effective%20at%20removing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-improve-indoor-air-quality%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindoor%20air%20pollution%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20average%20houseplant%2C%20Torbey%20and%20Mora%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20care%20about%20is%20putting%20nature%20at%20the%20center%20of%20innovation%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Torbey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHarnessing%20the%20power%20of%20bacteria%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228652%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20petri%20dish%20that's%20half%20purple%20and%20uncolonized%20on%20the%20left%20side%2C%20and%20pink%20and%20colonized%20by%20rows%20of%20small%20spots%20of%20bacteria%20on%20the%20right%20side%2C%20against%20a%20black%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662bd3f610dfcda40963e253%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20petri%20dish%20was%20cultured%20with%20Neoplants'%20bioengineered%20bacteria.%20But%20only%20the%20pink%20side%20was%20also%20swabbed%20with%20toluene%2C%20a%20VOC.%20The%20dots%20on%20that%20side%20are%20bacterial%20colonies%2C%20showing%20that%20this%20species%20can%20live%20off%20of%20VOCs.%3Cp%3ENeoplants%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENon-engineered%20houseplants%20are%20equipped%20with%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthese-houseplants-are-completely-idiot-proof-and-can-live-for-weeks-without-water-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enatural%20air-purifying%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20types%20are%20more%20effective%20than%20others.%20But%20research%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20would%20take%20hundreds%20of%20regular%20houseplants%20to%20purify%20the%20air%20inside%20a%201%2C500%20square-foot%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETorbey%20and%20Mora%20wanted%20to%20achieve%20air%20purification%20with%20a%20single%20houseplant.%20To%20do%20that%2C%20they%20hacked%20into%20the%20plant's%20microbiome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20targeted%20a%20strain%20of%20bacteria%20called%20Pseudomonas%20putida%2C%20which%20have%20a%20particular%20appetite%20for%20three%20common%20VOCs%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-risk-benzene-pollution-houston-channelview-jacintoport-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebenzene%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20toluene%2C%20and%20xylene.%20There%20are%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20types%20of%20VOCs%20that%20can%20be%20present%20in