3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663139980dfb1341e900d69a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223485%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStudent%20protesters%20at%20the%201985%20demonstrations%20at%20Columbia%20University.%3Cp%3EBarbara%20Alper%3B%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%201985%20protests%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demonstrations%20are%20reminiscent%20of%20those%20in%201985%2C%20when%20protesters%20and%20civil%20rights%20leaders%20were%20outraged%20over%20the%20apartheid%20regime%20in%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201978%2C%20the%20school's%20governing%20body%20had%20recommended%20selectively%20selling%20stocks%20of%20companies%20that%20had%20holdings%20in%20South%20Africa%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesmachine.nytimes.com%2Ftimesmachine%2F1978%2F05%2F07%2F110943821.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20New%20York%20Times%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%20Three%20hundred%20students%20had%20protested%20outside%20the%20meeting%2C%20calling%20for%20all%20the%20stocks%20to%20be%20divested%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20school's%201978%20recommendation%20didn't%20shut%20down%20the%20protests.%20In%20April%201985%2C%20the%20Coalition%20for%20a%20Free%20South%20Africa%20at%20the%20school%20organized%20a%20protest%20at%20Hamilton%20Hall%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.columbiaspectator.com%2Feye%2F2016%2F04%2F12%2Fmandela-hall%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Columbia%20Spectator%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20small%20demonstration%20quickly%20grew%20to%20thousands%20of%20supporters%2C%20the%20Spectator%20reported.%20Protesters%20there%20locked%20and%20chained%20the%20doors%20to%20Hamilton%20Hall%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20building%20now%20occupied%20by%20pro-Palestinian%20protesters%20%E2%80%94%20and%20demanded%20the%20school%20completely%20divest%20from%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20protests%20lasted%20on%20campus%20for%2021