%20third%20of%20the%20global%20population%2C%20and%20climatic%20changes%20in%20the%20region%20have%20major%20societal%20and%20economic%20impacts.%20The%20effects%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20more%20severe%20in%20and%20around%20India%20as%20the%20rise%20in%20seawater%20temperatures%20has%20been%20highest%20in%20the%20Northwestern%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20including%20the%20Arabian%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20led%20by%20Roxy%20Mathew%20Koll%20of%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Tropical%20Meteorology%20Pune%2C%20also%20states%20that%20the%20warming%20will%20contribute%20to%20rising%20sea%20levels%20and%20a%20reduction%20in%20marine%20productivity%2C%20all%20of%20which%20will%20threaten%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20people%20on%20the%20coast%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20dependent%20on%20fishing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESevere%20Weather%20Events%2C%20Permanent%20Heatwave%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublished%20by%20Elsevier%2C%20the%20study%20warns%20that%20the%20seasonal%20cycle%20of%20surface%20temperatures%20is%20projected%20to%20shift%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come%2C%20which%20may%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20extreme%20weather%20events%20over%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeasured%20as%20'maximum%20basin-average%20temperatures'%20the%20temperature%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20between%201980%20and%202020%20was%20between%2026%20degrees%20and%2028%20degrees%20Celsius%20throughout%20the%20year%20and%20the%20study%20has%20warned%20that%2C%20in%20a%20high%20emission%20scenario%2C%20even%20the%20minimum%20temperature%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20century%20will%20be%20above%2028%20degrees%20Celsius%20-%20between%2028.5%20degrees%20and%2030.7%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20states%20that%2C%20with%20ocean%20temperatures%20rising%2C%20extremely%20severe%20cyclones%20and%20heavy%20rainfall%20events%20-%20which%20have%20already%20gone%20up%20since%20the%201950s%20-%20are%20projected%20to%20only%20increase%20in%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20which%20is%20likely%20to%20contribute%20to%20such%20events%20is%20marine%20heatwaves%2C%20which%20are%20periods%20of%20extremely%20high%20temperatures%20in%20the%20ocean.%20These%20are%20expected%20to%20increase%20over%2010%20times%20from%2020%20days%20a%20year%20to%20a%20whopping%20220-250%2C%20pushing%20the%20tropical%20Indian%20Ocean%20into%20what%20the%20study%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bnear-permanent%20heatwave%20state%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarine%20heatwaves%20cause%20a%20rapid%20intensification%20of%20cyclones%2C%20where%20a%20cyclone%20goes%20from%20a%20depression%20to%20a%20severe%20category%20in%20just%20a%20few%20hours.%20They%20also%20lead%20to%20coral%20bleaching%20and%20the%20destruction%20of%20seagrass%20and%20kelp%20forests%2C%20which%20can%20have%20a%20major%20negative%20impact%20on%20the%20fisheries%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lead%20author%2C%20Roxy%20Matthew%20Koll%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20crucial%20to%20recognise%20that%20the%20impacts%20of%20these%20changes%20are%20not%20distant%20concerns%20for%20our%20grandchildren%20and%20future%20generations%20alone.%20As%20the%20current%20generation%2C%20we%20are%20already%20witnessing%20the%20repercussions%20firsthand.%20Monsoon%20floods%2C%20droughts%2C%20cyclones%2C%20and%20heatwaves%20over%20both%20land%20and%20ocean%20are%20increasingly%20affecting%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20extreme%20weather%20events%20will%20amplify%20in%20intensity%20and%20frequency%20before%20we%20reach%20the%20twilight%20of%20our%20time%20-%20unless%20decisive%20action%20to%20adapt%20and%20mitigate%20climate%20change%20is%20taken%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMonsoon%20Impact%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Ocean%20Dipole%2C%20a%20climate%20pattern%20that%20affects%20the%20monsoon%20and%20cyclone%20formation%2C%20is%20also%20predicted%20to%20change.%20The%20study%20says%20that%20the%20frequency%20of%20extreme%20dipole%20events%20is%20predicted%20to%20increase%20by%2066%25%20whereas%20moderate%20events%20will%20decrease%20by%2052%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%2021st%20century.%20This%20could%20spell%20bad%20news%20for%20monsoon-dependent%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20warmed%20at%20a%20rate%20of%201.2%20degrees%20Celsius%20per%20century%20in%20the%2070%20years%20between%201950%20and%202020%2C%20the%20study%20said%20climate%20models%20predict%20the%20warming%20will%20accelerate%20and%20go%20up%20to%20between%201.7%20and%203.8%20degrees%20Celsius%20until%202100.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20warming%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20the%20surface%20and%20extends%20to%20a%20depth%20of%202%2C000%20metres.%20%26quot%3BThe%20future%20increase%20in%20heat%20content%20is%20comparable%20to%20adding%20the%20energy%20equivalent%20of%20one%20Hiroshima%20atomic%20bomb%20detonation%20every%20second%2C%20all%20day%2C%20every%20day%2C%20for%20a%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Koll%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncreasing%20heat%20in%20the%20ocean%20also%20contributes%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20sea%20levels.%20The%20study%20said%20thermal%20expansion%20of%20water%20contributes%20to%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20sea%20level%20rise%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20which%20is%20even%20more%20than%20the%20contribution%20from%20the%20melting%20of%20glaciers%20and%20sea%20ice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAcidification%20To%20Increase%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOcean%20acidification%20is%20also%20predicted%20to%20go%20up%2C%20with%20pH%20levels%20at%20the%20surface%20decreasing%20from%20above%208.1%20to%20below%207.7%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20projected%20changes%20in%20pH%20may%20be%20detrimental%20to%20the%20marine%20ecosystem%20since%20many%20marine%20organisms-particularly%20corals%20and%20organisms%20that%20depend%20on%20calcification%20to%20build%20and%20maintain%20their%20shells-are%20sensitive%20to%20the%20change%20in%20ocean%20acidity.%20The%20change%20may%20be%20easier%20to%20fathom%20when%20we%20realize%20that%20a%200.1%20fall%20in%20human%20blood%20pH%20can%20result%20in%20rather%20profound%20health%20consequences%20and%20multiple-organ%20failure%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Koll%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20calls%20for%20taking%20a%20multifaceted%20approach%20to%20addressing%20the%20problem%20of%20warming%2C%20including%20decreasing%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20and%20the%20authors%20have%20also%20asked%20for%20action%20to%20be%20taken%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20a%20climate%20change%20hotspot%2C%20faces%20rapid%20and%20strong%20increases%20in%20marine%20heatwave%20frequency%20and%20intensity%20unless%20global%20CO2%20emissions%20are%20substantially%20cut%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20Frolicher%2C%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714491960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fnujaaga_ocean-reuters_625x300_07_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-ocean-likely-to-see-near-permanent-heatwave-study-5559209%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sounding%20a%20warning%2C%20a%20study%20has%20revealed%20that%20the%20warming%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20is%20going%20to%20lead%20to%20the%20worsening%20of%20severe%20cyclones%20and%20heavy%20rainfall%20events%20and%20that%20the%20world's%203rd-largest%20water%20body%20is%20moving%20to%20a%20near-permanent%20heatwave%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-ocean-likely-to-see-near-permanent-heatwave-study-5559209%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-ocean-likely-to-see-near-permanent-heatwave-study-5559209%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian